vocation /vəʊˈkeɪʃən/

(vocations) 

1. N-VAR If you have a vocation , you have a strong feeling that you are especially suited to do a particular job or to fulfill a particular role in life, especially one that involves helping other people. 使命感 

例： It could well be that he has a real vocation. 他很可能有种真正的使命感。 

2. N-VAR If you refer to your job or profession as your vocation , you feel that you are particularly suited to it. 适合的职业 

例： Her vocation is her work as an actress. 她适合的职业就是当演员。

</div>

